description.narrative: By 2021, parents and families have enhanced knowledge and skills on nutrition, care, protection and development of young children, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Early Childhood Development, Early Childhood Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, children between the ages 0 to 5 years are progressively cared for through quality Early Child Development (ECD) services and in protective and nurturing family environments.

description.narrative: The quality of parenting services provided by the government is strengthened with support from UNICEF. Parents are engaged in participatory sessions on child development at ECD centers, and ECD professionals are equipped with guidelines for home visits to help them better understand the families' issues and address them effectively. Taking advantage of the high social media usage in the country, the new mobile parenting communication platform “Early Moments Matter on Mobile”, powered by RapidPro, launched with DoH to reach parents of children 0-6 years with information that they need to provide their young children with the best start in life. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
